Description: 0 false 18 pt 18 pt 0 0 false false false Fender Special Edition Deluxe Ash Telecaster with Pickup Upgrades MIM Here is a 2014 Fender FSR Butterscotch / Blonde Ash Telecaster in Excellent Plus condition. You have to look really hard to find any imperfections – it’s pretty close to being new! The pickups have been upgraded to: Bridge: Fender Custom Shop '51 Nocaster Tele Bridge Neck: Seymour Duncan 59 Neck SH-1N – the cover was added and is not soldered on. It is a two conductor. I also replaced the original tone cap with a Mallory “orange drop”. The only thing I want to bring to your attention is that in the middle position, the pickups are currently “out of phase”. Since the neck pickup is two conductors, I wasn’t able to get the polarity correct. So please be aware of that – great if you like that “Greenie Tone”. You may be able to get in back in phase by reversing the wires on the bridge pickup but if my memory is correct, there is a separate (third) ground wire on it and that may have to be disconnected. My inclination on the MIM (Mexican) guitars is to part them out and sell them but this plays really great, has great tone, and the note ring nicely over the entire fingerboard. I just hardly ever play it and want the funds for another purchase. Includes the original Fender gig bag. Weighs 7lbs 8oz. Note: in the picture that shows the side of the neck where it meets the body – there is a mark right after the 19th fret – this is not a crack, it is a flame pattern in the maple grain.The guitar will be shipped with insurance and will require a signature - I will cover these cost and the buyer will be responsible for the shipping costs. From Fender The Fender Special Edition Deluxe Ash Telecaster features the best of the old and the new: a butterscotch blonde finish, a fast-action maple neck, cast/sealed machine heads, two classic single-coil pickups, and a 3-barrel string-thru-body bridge. Since its introduction in the early '50s, guitarists in all musical genres have relied on the Fender Telecaster guitar for its powerful tone and smooth playability.
